00:51:06.795 --> 00:51:08.475
I have been teaching, practicing,

956
00:51:08.575 --> 00:51:11.475
and writing about internet law since the 1990s,

957
00:51:12.015 --> 00:51:13.435
and I appreciate the opportunity

958
00:51:13.435 --> 00:51:14.835
to share my views with you today.

959
00:51:15.945 --> 00:51:18.305
I impose laws that force internet publishers

960
00:51:18.365 --> 00:51:20.625
to distinguish adults from children online,

961
00:51:20.935 --> 00:51:23.785
what I call a segregation requirement, so

962
00:51:23.785 --> 00:51:26.705
that segregated children will have restricted access

963
00:51:26.705 --> 00:51:28.785
to online information, services

964
00:51:28.925 --> 00:51:31.945
or tools, what I call the suppression requirement.

965
00:51:32.695 --> 00:51:34.255
I will mention four general points

966
00:51:34.255 --> 00:51:36.335
before I turn to my substantive objections.

967
00:51:37.225 --> 00:51:40.335
First, there's a semantic confusion about the differences

968
00:51:40.335 --> 00:51:43.415
between age authentication, my preferred term,

969
00:51:44.075 --> 00:51:47.695
age assurance, age estimation, and age verification.

970
00:51:48.475 --> 00:51:49.815
The mechanics of each vary,

971
00:51:50.075 --> 00:51:52.375
but my objections apply equally to all of them.

972
00:51:53.815 --> 00:51:57.035
Second, age authentication is a prerequisite

973
00:51:57.415 --> 00:52:00.795
for any child's safety or harm policies.

974
00:52:01.085 --> 00:52:04.035
Publishers can't protect children if publishers

975
00:52:04.095 --> 00:52:05.195
do not know who they are.

976
00:52:05.825 --> 00:52:08.075
Thus, any online child safety

977
00:52:08.335 --> 00:52:12.435
or child harm regulatory intervention must necessarily

978
00:52:12.665 --> 00:52:15.075
address the problems of age authentication.

979
00:52:15.965 --> 00:52:19.755
Third age authentication processes always impact adults.

980
00:52:20.555 --> 00:52:21.995
Everyone must be age authenticated

981
00:52:22.055 --> 00:52:23.195
to segregate the children.

982
00:52:24.925 --> 00:52:27.025
Fourth, it is a false equivalency

983
00:52:27.085 --> 00:52:29.945
to analogize online age authentication

984
00:52:30.045 --> 00:52:33.945
to offline age authentication, for example, compared

985
00:52:33.945 --> 00:52:35.545
to offline age authentication,

986
00:52:36.205 --> 00:52:38.745
online publishers incur greater marginal costs

987
00:52:38.745 --> 00:52:40.185
to do the authentication.

988
00:52:40.805 --> 00:52:42.905
And in the process, consumers are exposed

989
00:52:42.925 --> 00:52:46.065
to unprecedented privacy and security risks.

990
00:52:47.205 --> 00:52:50.625
To maximize my time, I will highlight 13 objections

991
00:52:50.765 --> 00:52:53.025
to segregate and suppress policies.

992
00:52:53.675 --> 00:52:56.985
Point number one, as New Zealand privacy Commissioner

993
00:52:56.985 --> 00:52:58.785
Michael Webster recently said,

994
00:52:59.165 --> 00:53:02.545
age authentication will quote, require the collection

995
00:53:02.545 --> 00:53:04.905
of large volumes of personal information

996
00:53:05.165 --> 00:53:06.545
of social media users.

997
00:53:07.435 --> 00:53:09.905
Every currently available commercial offering

998
00:53:10.215 --> 00:53:11.505
invades consumer privacy.

999
00:53:12.635 --> 00:53:17.265
Point two, requiring children to routinely age authenticate

1000
00:53:17.325 --> 00:53:20.065
as they navigate the internet will teach children

1001
00:53:20.495 --> 00:53:23.505
that privacy invasions are the unavoidable cost

1002
00:53:23.805 --> 00:53:27.325
of accessing vital information and services in our society.

1003
00:53:27.835 --> 00:53:29.725
This lesson will permanently distort

1004
00:53:29.825 --> 00:53:31.205
how children view privacy.

1005
00:53:32.925 --> 00:53:35.515
Point three, the routine disclosure

1006
00:53:35.575 --> 00:53:38.115
of highly sensitive personal information such

1007
00:53:38.115 --> 00:53:40.915
as biometric scans or driver's license information.

1008
00:53:41.455 --> 00:53:44.115
As part of any age authentication process,

1009
00:53:44.785 --> 00:53:47.835
unavoidably puts consumers at greater security risk.

1010
00:53:48.535 --> 00:53:52.515
Indeed, numerous authenticators have already suffered major

1011
00:53:52.625 --> 00:53:55.835
data security breaches of their authentication data.

1012
00:53:56.775 --> 00:53:59.955
If the goal of, uh, age authentication is to kill,

1013
00:54:00.145 --> 00:54:04.035
keep children safer, it is cruelly ironic to force children

1014
00:54:04.175 --> 00:54:07.595
to regularly disclose highly sensitive private information

1015
00:54:08.015 --> 00:54:09.355
and increase their exposure

1016
00:54:09.815 --> 00:54:12.955
to potentially life-changing data security violations.

1017
00:54:14.245 --> 00:54:16.195
Point four, children know how

1018
00:54:16.195 --> 00:54:18.315
to defeat age authentication barriers using

1019
00:54:18.315 --> 00:54:19.755
freight fake credentials.

1020
00:54:20.025 --> 00:54:22.915
