Okay. Thank you, Nathan.

3301
02:58:06.265 --> 02:58:07.665
I think that that's, um, all we've got

3302
02:58:07.665 --> 02:58:08.745
time for this afternoon.

3303
02:58:08.745 --> 02:58:10.545
Really appreciate, um, your submission. Thank you.

3304
02:58:10.595 --> 02:58:12.225
Thank you all. Thank you. Uh, present.

3305
02:58:13.995 --> 02:58:16.245
Okay, members, we are now moving

3306
02:58:16.945 --> 02:58:19.085
to the free speech Union

3307
02:58:21.045 --> 02:58:22.065
who are online.

3308
02:58:23.575 --> 02:58:26.635
Hi Steph. Uh, thanks for joining us this afternoon.

3309
02:58:26.925 --> 02:58:28.755
We've, um, got you with us for 10 minutes,

3310
02:58:29.215 --> 02:58:30.435
so I'll hand straight over to you.

3311
02:58:30.855 --> 02:58:33.875
Lovely, thank you. All right, well, um, thank you

3312
02:58:33.895 --> 02:58:35.635
for the opportunity to speak with you today.

3313
02:58:35.775 --> 02:58:37.515
Um, we recognize that the challenge

3314
02:58:37.585 --> 02:58:41.035
that presents the select, sorry presently faces,

3315
02:58:41.095 --> 02:58:43.235
the Select committee here isn't a straightforward one.

3316
02:58:43.815 --> 02:58:46.595
The digital public square is a complex space to navigate,

3317
02:58:46.595 --> 02:58:49.115
and one of the great challenges of our time appears to be

3318
02:58:49.115 --> 02:58:51.315
how we effectively translate critical pillars

3319
02:58:51.315 --> 02:58:52.595
of our democratic principles

3320
02:58:52.615 --> 02:58:54.315
and the human rights on which they rely

3321
02:58:54.315 --> 02:58:55.355
into digital settings.

3322
02:58:56.295 --> 02:58:58.875
In recognizing this complexity, we also suggest

3323
02:58:58.915 --> 02:59:00.395
that no solution will be perfect.

3324
02:59:01.255 --> 02:59:02.435
We understand and accept

3325
02:59:02.435 --> 02:59:04.835
that there is content on the internet, the consumption

3326
02:59:04.855 --> 02:59:07.155
of which poses genuine psychological risk

3327
02:59:07.175 --> 02:59:08.555
to users who engage with it.

3328
02:59:09.145 --> 02:59:10.755
However, we think that it is vital

3329
02:59:10.755 --> 02:59:13.395
that these risks are considered clearly and proportionally

3330
02:59:13.495 --> 02:59:14.875
and are empirically verified.

3331
02:59:15.725 --> 02:59:18.355
Today, we'll outline several of our foremost concerns.

3332
02:59:18.355 --> 02:59:20.395
However, we would also welcome the opportunity

3333
02:59:20.495 --> 02:59:22.755
for continued engagement with the committee on this issue

3334
02:59:23.765 --> 02:59:26.275
being that we are the free speech union, our primary concern

3335
02:59:26.275 --> 02:59:28.755
and contribution to this issue is in recognizing the

3336
02:59:28.755 --> 02:59:30.155
potential threats to free speech

3337
02:59:30.155 --> 02:59:31.515
that might emerge out of this work.

3338
02:59:32.215 --> 02:59:34.195
We caution that there is a substantial risk

3339
02:59:34.195 --> 02:59:37.315
that any digital intervention strategies that are adopted

3340
02:59:37.375 --> 02:59:39.995
to minimize harm will undermine the rights

3341
02:59:39.995 --> 02:59:41.195
that are enshrined to Kiwis

3342
02:59:41.195 --> 02:59:42.675
through the New Zealand Bill of Rights Act.

3343
02:59:43.425 --> 02:59:46.235
This is almost necessarily the case since any conceivable

3344
02:59:46.235 --> 02:59:48.875
digital intervention will inevitably risk both false

3345
02:59:49.195 --> 02:59:50.435
positives and false negatives,

3346
02:59:50.775 --> 02:59:53.675
either non-problematic content will be captured in rejected

3347
02:59:54.295 --> 02:59:57.275
or problematic content will not be captured, or both.

3348
02:59:58.125 --> 02:59:59.995
Every instance of a false positive

3349
03:00:00.015 --> 03:00:02.195
or rejected content will represent a breach

3350
03:00:02.215 --> 03:00:04.595
of an individual's rights to freedom of expression.

3351
03:00:05.225 --> 03:00:06.715
This is a serious side effect

3352
03:00:06.715 --> 03:00:08.035
and it shouldn't be taken lightly.

3353
03:00:09.155 --> 03:00:10.275
Interventions that take a broad

3354
03:00:10.275 --> 03:00:12.675
and blunt approach to to digital blocking

3355
03:00:12.735 --> 03:00:14.475
and interference are further likely

3356
03:00:14.535 --> 03:00:16.715
to increase the occurrences of false positives.

3357
03:00:17.015 --> 03:00:19.835
And so there simply must be avoided to maintain adherence

3358
03:00:19.895 --> 03:00:22.075
to lawful speech and consistency with the Bill

3359
03:00:22.075 --> 03:00:25.235
of Rights Act, we acknowledge

3360
03:00:25.235 --> 03:00:27.555
and share the genuine concerns for young New Zealanders

3361
03:00:27.555 --> 03:00:29.515
that many of our submitters will have shared today

3362
03:00:29.515 --> 03:00:32.595
and will continue to share today about the plethora

3363
03:00:32.595 --> 03:00:34.395
of adverse impacts on our young people

3364
03:00:34.825 --> 03:00:37.555
that they're experiencing as a result of exposure

3365
03:00:37.575 --> 03:00:39.035
to damaging content online.

3366
03:00:39.785 --> 03:00:41.235
This is a concerning situation

3367
03:00:41.235 --> 03:00:43.395
that we really welcome the conversation about the issue.

3368
03:00:44.415 --> 03:00:46.595
The challenge before us lies in finding a way

3369
03:00:46.595 --> 03:00:49.155
to address legitimate concerns about protecting children

3370
03:00:49.665 --> 03:00:51.555
from exposure to damaging content

3371
03:00:52.265 --> 03:00:53.915
without compromising the speech

3372
03:00:53.915 --> 03:00:55.995
and privacy rights of adults in the process.

3373
03:00:57.225 --> 03:00:58.635
Many intervention strategies

3374
03:00:58.635 --> 03:01:01.445
that may be effective in preventing children from accessing

3375
03:01:01.765 --> 03:01:05.325
damaging content would result in intolerable collateral

3376
03:01:05.325 --> 03:01:07.685
damage to freedoms that are guaranteed to New Zealanders

3377
03:01:07.685 --> 03:01:08.765
through the Bill of Rights Act.

3378
03:01:09.665 --> 03:01:11.805
In considering this difficult balance, we caution

3379
03:01:11.805 --> 03:01:15.045
that strategies that are adopted must not come at the cost

3380
03:01:15.045 --> 03:01:17.645
of technological overreach, censorship,

3381
03:01:17.745 --> 03:01:20.045
and mass surveillance for the community at large.

3382
03:01:20.775 --> 03:01:24.145
Context such as this one that evoke high emotionality

3383
03:01:24.165 --> 03:01:26.545
and a strong sense of protectiveness are

3384
03:01:26.545 --> 03:01:28.505
where our commitments to freedom are most challenged

3385
03:01:29.005 --> 03:01:31.345
and mindful of this, we urge that this is not an issue

3386
03:01:31.345 --> 03:01:34.545
to approach with haste and reactiveness, but caution

3387
03:01:34.605 --> 03:01:37.345
and wisdom, the potential side effects

3388
03:01:37.345 --> 03:01:39.705
of any intervention must be thoroughly considered

3389
03:01:39.965 --> 03:01:41.265
and action should not be taken

3390
03:01:41.265 --> 03:01:43.665
where those side effects are simply too costly.

3391
03:01:45.465 --> 03:01:48.125
At the Free Speech Union, we regularly encounter cases

3392
03:01:48.135 --> 03:01:51.925
where vague and over broad definitions in legislation codes

3393
03:01:51.925 --> 03:01:54.765
or policies result in infringements on individuals freedoms.

3394
03:01:55.675 --> 03:01:57.445
Many of these are grounded in the suggestion

3395
03:01:57.445 --> 03:02:00.085
that the views expressed by one party were perceived

3396
03:02:00.085 --> 03:02:01.285
to be harmful to the other,

3397
03:02:01.865 --> 03:02:04.405
and can variously lead to individuals being sanctioned,

3398
03:02:04.405 --> 03:02:06.245
dismissed deregistered find

3399
03:02:06.305 --> 03:02:09.545
or even arrested vague language opens the door

3400
03:02:09.545 --> 03:02:11.785
to weaponization and asymmetric justice

3401
03:02:12.285 --> 03:02:15.705
and has a chilling effect on those individuals on, sorry,

3402
03:02:15.705 --> 03:02:17.545
on those who see individuals silenced

3403
03:02:17.545 --> 03:02:19.545
and punished for expressing an alternative perspective.

3404
03:02:20.365 --> 03:02:21.625
We therefore implore the committee

3405
03:02:21.645 --> 03:02:23.345
to consider terminology very carefully.

3406
03:02:24.405 --> 03:02:25.705
An overboard definition

3407
03:02:25.705 --> 03:02:28.305
of harm will almost inevitably increase the frequency

3408
03:02:28.305 --> 03:02:31.585
of false positives, and this would end up capturing a great

3409
03:02:31.585 --> 03:02:35.265
deal of potentially offensive, controversial, unpopular,

3410
03:02:35.365 --> 03:02:38.305
or awful, but lawful content that are all within the scope

3411
03:02:38.305 --> 03:02:39.305
of freedom of expression.

3412
03:02:40.015 --> 03:02:42.745
Further, it would use up resources on these situations

3413
03:02:42.745 --> 03:02:45.545
where those same resources could instead be invested in

3414
03:02:45.545 --> 03:02:47.785
targeting content that corresponds with illegal activity,

3415
03:02:48.335 --> 03:02:50.825
such as child sexual abuse, material terrorism,

3416
03:02:50.935 --> 03:02:52.385
organized crime, and so on.

3417
03:02:54.085 --> 03:02:56.585
The Free Speech Union has raised concerns in numerous

3418
03:02:56.705 --> 03:02:59.385
contexts in recent years about an over calibration

3419
03:02:59.385 --> 03:03:01.505
or concept creep of the notion of harm

3420
03:03:01.925 --> 03:03:04.545
and serious harm, such that, for example,

3421
03:03:04.545 --> 03:03:06.025
raising a contentious issue

3422
03:03:06.025 --> 03:03:07.905
for discussion is perceived as threatening.

3423
03:03:08.325 --> 03:03:11.345
And this interpreted threat is subsequently characterized

3424
03:03:11.365 --> 03:03:14.465
as violence and used to suppress both robust discussion

3425
03:03:14.465 --> 03:03:18.115
and the dissenters themselves over calibrating our threat

3426
03:03:18.115 --> 03:03:21.195
detection for harm and suppressing expression in the process

3427
03:03:21.335 --> 03:03:23.995
stands to have serious consequences for our communities.

3428
03:03:24.285 --> 03:03:26.595
Since it blurs the lines between free speech

3429
03:03:26.595 --> 03:03:30.275
and action without allowing the bandwidth for freedom

3430
03:03:30.295 --> 03:03:31.995
of speech, the risk exists

3431
03:03:31.995 --> 03:03:35.235
that physical violence will increasingly be recognized

3432
03:03:35.235 --> 03:03:37.635
as a reasonable response to words that are perceived

3433
03:03:37.635 --> 03:03:38.755
to be hate, hateful,

3434
03:03:38.755 --> 03:03:42.075
or threatening Without the ability to speak one's mind,

3435
03:03:42.075 --> 03:03:43.395
people may increasingly feel

3436
03:03:43.395 --> 03:03:45.315
that the only option left is to act it out.

3437
03:03:47.025 --> 03:03:48.235
This is a troubling trend

3438
03:03:48.235 --> 03:03:49.595
that we're witnessing internationally

3439
03:03:49.615 --> 03:03:51.275
and we desperately hope to avoid here.

3440
03:03:52.015 --> 03:03:54.555
We therefore advise that any threshold for harm needs

3441
03:03:54.555 --> 03:03:56.075
to be thought through very carefully.

3442
03:03:56.735 --> 03:03:59.165
Having a clear distinction between harmful words

3443
03:03:59.185 --> 03:04:01.125
and damaging content is essential.

3444
03:04:01.545 --> 03:04:03.805
And this is especially the case in the digital square

3445
03:04:03.815 --> 03:04:06.445
where we know that many violent offenders have previously

3446
03:04:06.445 --> 03:04:07.645
been radicalized online.

3447
03:04:09.175 --> 03:04:10.765
We've already noted that the complexity

3448
03:04:10.765 --> 03:04:12.165
of this challenge means that there will be no

3449
03:04:12.165 --> 03:04:13.605
perfect solution to addressing it.

3450
03:04:14.235 --> 03:04:16.405
This means that it simply has to be considered in terms

3451
03:04:16.405 --> 03:04:18.565
of trade-offs, the least bad scenario,

3452
03:04:18.785 --> 03:04:21.245
or the approach with minimal costs or risks involved.

3453
03:04:22.105 --> 03:04:25.005
We again, caution that the top-down implementation of broad

3454
03:04:25.005 --> 03:04:28.165
and blunt instruments will have intolerable consequences and

3455
03:04:28.165 --> 03:04:29.285
therefore need to be avoided.

3456
03:04:30.245 --> 03:04:32.485
Blocking through internet infrastructure itself is the

3457
03:04:32.485 --> 03:04:34.325
broadest and bluntest possible approach,

3458
03:04:34.825 --> 03:04:37.405
and the risks of collateral damage in a high rate

3459
03:04:37.405 --> 03:04:40.045
of false positives makes this approach the most problematic

3460
03:04:40.045 --> 03:04:42.325
when weighed against the cost to New Zealanders freedoms.

3461
03:04:43.285 --> 03:04:45.655
Placing the onus on social media companies

3462
03:04:45.655 --> 03:04:48.015
to filter content is also an approach to avoid.

3463
03:04:48.485 --> 03:04:50.695
They themselves do not have effective systems in place

3464
03:04:50.695 --> 03:04:52.335
to address content moderation

3465
03:04:53.155 --> 03:04:55.855
and recent revelations about the traumatizing toll on the

3466
03:04:55.855 --> 03:04:57.135
low paid workers who are charged

3467
03:04:57.135 --> 03:04:59.335
with manual content moderation confirmed

3468
03:04:59.335 --> 03:05:00.695
that this is not a viable approach.

3469
03:05:01.885 --> 03:05:04.255
Instead of these top down measures, we advocate

3470
03:05:04.255 --> 03:05:06.135
that the role of government could helpfully be

3471
03:05:06.135 --> 03:05:07.935
to enable ground up approaches.

3472
03:05:08.605 --> 03:05:11.935
This would involve the provision of opt-in user end tools

3473
03:05:12.075 --> 03:05:13.255
for individuals and parents,

3474
03:05:13.435 --> 03:05:16.615
and the commensurate digital literacy education.

3475
03:05:17.675 --> 03:05:18.775
We would encourage the committee

3476
03:05:18.795 --> 03:05:21.135
to explore potential options for resourcing these tools

3477
03:05:21.595 --> 03:05:24.175
and running campaigns to raise awareness about the options

3478
03:05:24.175 --> 03:05:25.655
that are available throughout New Zealand.

3479
03:05:26.425 --> 03:05:28.935
Since these do not entail any adverse consequences

3480
03:05:28.955 --> 03:05:29.975
for Kiwi's rights,

3481
03:05:30.225 --> 03:05:32.975
these could be readily implemented without a clear problem

3482
03:05:32.975 --> 03:05:34.335
definition for online harm.

3483
03:05:34.845 --> 03:05:36.655
Effectively, work could start on this tomorrow.

3484
03:05:38.025 --> 03:05:40.565
Opt-in tools would give New Zealanders control over their

3485
03:05:40.565 --> 03:05:41.805
own digital experiences

3486
03:05:42.545 --> 03:05:44.285
and empower consumers of digital content

3487
03:05:44.345 --> 03:05:46.765
to make their own decisions about the digital environment

3488
03:05:46.765 --> 03:05:47.845
that they wish to curate

3489
03:05:47.845 --> 03:05:49.325
for themselves and for their children.

3490
03:05:50.785 --> 03:05:53.045
Opt-in tools are available for both networks

3491
03:05:53.045 --> 03:05:54.165
and individual devices,

3492
03:05:54.785 --> 03:05:56.165
and there are a range of options for

3493
03:05:56.165 --> 03:05:57.805
how these settings can be controlled.

3494
03:05:59.065 --> 03:06:01.285
We recognize that this approach will not prevent the

3495
03:06:01.405 --> 03:06:02.565
exchange of all content that is

3496
03:06:02.565 --> 03:06:03.925
potentially damaging to consume.

3497
03:06:04.315 --> 03:06:05.405
However, we suggest

3498
03:06:05.405 --> 03:06:07.405
that this approach provides the greatest way forward

3499
03:06:07.525 --> 03:06:09.365
that balances minimizing damage

3500
03:06:09.425 --> 03:06:10.725
and upholding New Zealander's

3501
03:06:10.725 --> 03:06:11.885
right to freedom of expression.

3502
03:06:12.955 --> 03:06:14.405
This approach provides a solution

3503
03:06:14.405 --> 03:06:16.725
to young New Zealanders accidentally stumbling into

3504
03:06:16.725 --> 03:06:19.765
disturbing content while avoiding the potential collateral

3505
03:06:19.785 --> 03:06:21.805
damage of all New Zealanders being subjected

3506
03:06:21.805 --> 03:06:23.485
to mass surveillance and heavy restrictions

3507
03:06:23.485 --> 03:06:24.605
on their expressive freedoms.

3508
03:06:25.345 --> 03:06:27.685
It enables transparency and gives the user

3509
03:06:27.785 --> 03:06:30.525
or the guardian the ability to decide what kinds

3510
03:06:30.525 --> 03:06:32.805
of content they want to consume and what they don't.

3511
03:06:33.935 --> 03:06:36.925
Above all though, we really caution against the use of broad

3512
03:06:36.925 --> 03:06:39.005
and blunt instruments, um, terminology

3513
03:06:39.065 --> 03:06:41.125
and tools that stand to have serious ramifications

3514
03:06:41.125 --> 03:06:43.725
for New Zealanders legal rights, not least their rights

3515
03:06:43.725 --> 03:06:44.845
to freedom of expression.

3516
03:06:47.395 --> 03:06:49.295
Thanks, Steve. First question from Grant

3517
03:06:49.295 --> 03:06:50.295
McCullum. Yeah, thanks.

3518
03:06:50.295 --> 03:06:51.895
Um, question,

3519
03:06:51.895 --> 03:06:54.415
given this is an inquiry into the on Young,

3520
03:06:54.515 --> 03:06:56.605
the Young New Zealanders encounter online,

3521
03:06:57.355 --> 03:07:01.325
does the Free Speech Union have any, see any difference

3522
03:07:01.325 --> 03:07:05.525
between, uh, a, a young person's, uh, a young person

3523
