some improved, uh, justice around the outcomes

5553
05:15:20.495 --> 05:15:21.675
of this type of harm.

5554
05:15:24.445 --> 05:15:25.445
Thank you.

5555
05:15:26.605 --> 05:15:29.395
Thank you, Tracy. Uh, grant McCullum.

5556
05:15:29.825 --> 05:15:31.035
Yeah. Uh, thank you, Tracy.

5557
05:15:31.215 --> 05:15:34.995
Uh, just, um, do you think if we could create a, uh,

5558
05:15:35.115 --> 05:15:37.675
a safe environment for, for people on young,

5559
05:15:37.675 --> 05:15:41.235
younger people on 16, to have an online interaction, like,

5560
05:15:41.295 --> 05:15:45.675
you know, to prevent where a place where, um, predators

5561
05:15:45.675 --> 05:15:48.795
and so forth couldn't access, would you think that would be,

5562
05:15:48.855 --> 05:15:50.755
um, a, a, a useful thing?

5563
05:15:52.895 --> 05:15:56.155
Uh, I don't know if there is such a, a thing.

5564
05:15:56.175 --> 05:15:58.315
The, these predators are so strategic.

5565
05:15:59.435 --> 05:16:01.715
I don't know how the controls

5566
05:16:02.635 --> 05:16:04.705
would work in that environment.

5567
05:16:06.115 --> 05:16:10.975
Um, we also need to empower our children what

5568
05:16:10.995 --> 05:16:15.345
to look for any signs of, uh, harm

5569
05:16:15.375 --> 05:16:16.545
that may be occurring.

5570
05:16:16.845 --> 05:16:21.145
The, because they're so subtle, these, these changes

5571
05:16:21.685 --> 05:16:23.385
in communication.

5572
05:16:24.895 --> 05:16:29.485
Uh, children need to be more aware of

5573
05:16:31.075 --> 05:16:32.445
that type of communication,

5574
05:16:32.665 --> 05:16:35.365
how quickly it can change. Here we go.

5575
05:16:36.255 --> 05:16:38.765
Thank you. Uh, thank you, Tracy.

5576
05:16:38.905 --> 05:16:40.405
We appreciate the time you've, uh, had

5577
05:16:40.405 --> 05:16:42.485
with us this afternoon, um,

5578
05:16:42.625 --> 05:16:45.205
and for sharing your experience and your recommendations.

5579
05:16:45.535 --> 05:16:48.925
Thank you so much. We're now gonna move, uh,

5580
05:16:48.945 --> 05:16:50.685
to the office of the privacy commissioner.

5581
05:16:50.755 --> 05:16:53.805
Michael's here with us, um, in the room.

5582
05:16:53.995 --> 05:16:57.355
Michael, I know that you, um, know the drill.

5583
05:16:57.815 --> 05:16:59.435
Uh, we've got 10 minutes with you this afternoon,

5584
05:16:59.435 --> 05:17:01.075
including any time for questions.

5585
05:17:03.715 --> 05:17:04.815
Uh, thank you, Mr. Chair.

5586
05:17:05.665 --> 05:17:09.085
Uh, I welcome, uh, this broad ranging inquiry

5587
05:17:09.795 --> 05:17:12.085
into the harm New Zealanders encounter online.

5588
05:17:12.625 --> 05:17:14.005
Uh, in fact, we've, uh,

5589
05:17:14.325 --> 05:17:16.445
recently completed our 2025 privacy survey.

5590
05:17:17.025 --> 05:17:20.845
And one of the findings from that was that around two thirds

5591
05:17:20.905 --> 05:17:23.725
of respondents were concerned about young

5592
05:17:23.725 --> 05:17:25.045
people and social media.

5593
05:17:25.985 --> 05:17:27.405
Of course, as you've heard already,

5594
05:17:27.425 --> 05:17:31.005
the online world presents both opportunities, uh,

5595
05:17:31.345 --> 05:17:32.885
and risks for young people.

5596
05:17:33.185 --> 05:17:35.365
And this, of course, from my perspective,

5597
05:17:35.365 --> 05:17:36.965
includes risks to privacy.

5598
05:17:37.865 --> 05:17:41.485
Uh, overall, we agree that regulatory work is needed, uh,

5599
05:17:41.485 --> 05:17:44.165
with a measured and evidence-based approach, for example.

5600
05:17:44.705 --> 05:17:47.965
Uh, and in particular in relation to age assurance.

5601
05:17:48.905 --> 05:17:51.765
Uh, my role as privacy commissioner includes monitoring

5602
05:17:51.785 --> 05:17:54.165
policy and technology developments

5603
05:17:54.165 --> 05:17:56.885
that have significant impacts on New Zealander's privacy,

5604
05:17:57.505 --> 05:17:59.285
uh, whether that be what happens online,

5605
05:17:59.785 --> 05:18:00.965
ai, all those sorts of areas.

5606
05:18:01.865 --> 05:18:04.485
Uh, you've heard a range of concerns, obviously already

5607
05:18:05.355 --> 05:18:08.265
about the harms young people face online.

5608
05:18:08.445 --> 05:18:11.185
Uh, you've heard mixed views on policy responses.

5609
05:18:11.805 --> 05:18:15.585
Uh, and I just want to, I guess, make one main point,

5610
05:18:15.585 --> 05:18:18.905
which is that any view of the, of the policy problems, uh,

5611
05:18:18.905 --> 05:18:21.705
and potential responses here must also carefully

5612
05:18:22.065 --> 05:18:23.425
consider privacy.

5613
05:18:24.285 --> 05:18:26.625
Uh, privacy is a critical aspect

5614
05:18:26.625 --> 05:18:30.825
of the risks young people face online, uh, already

5615
05:18:30.965 --> 05:18:34.265
how their data is collected, uh, who it's shared with,

5616
05:18:34.685 --> 05:18:36.145
and what it can be used for.

5617
05:18:36.765 --> 05:18:38.985
Uh, the Office of the Privacy Commissioner

5618
05:18:38.985 --> 05:18:40.865
through the Privacy Act already, uh,

5619
05:18:41.045 --> 05:18:44.705
has a regulatory role in relation, uh, to, uh,

5620
05:18:44.725 --> 05:18:47.985
the online world, uh, for everybody who takes part in that.

5621
05:18:48.485 --> 05:18:51.865
And, for example, we see things like, uh, targeted harms,

5622
05:18:52.325 --> 05:18:55.545
uh, like bullying, grooming, and impersonation.

5623
05:18:55.565 --> 05:18:58.945
And they all start, of course, with personal information

5624
05:18:59.885 --> 05:19:02.705
as do, uh, scatter gun harms, such

5625
05:19:02.765 --> 05:19:06.105
as automated cyber attacks and unwanted marketing.

5626
05:19:06.925 --> 05:19:09.025
So, privacy, uh, is critical

5627
05:19:09.025 --> 05:19:11.785
to understanding the policy options, whether those options,

5628
05:19:12.365 --> 05:19:14.025
uh, are safe, are effective,

5629
05:19:14.025 --> 05:19:17.185
and reliable enough to earn New Zealanders, uh, buy-in.

5630
05:19:18.255 --> 05:19:20.935
I know of course, that there is interest in mandating, uh,

5631
05:19:21.015 --> 05:19:23.655
a minimum age for some online services

5632
05:19:23.835 --> 05:19:26.015
and variations of this policy, uh,

5633
05:19:26.075 --> 05:19:29.455
how being tried in the eu, the uk, and Australia,

5634
05:19:30.275 --> 05:19:32.255
and there is of course, the private members bill

5635
05:19:32.255 --> 05:19:35.415
with the same, any age restriction, uh,

5636
05:19:35.435 --> 05:19:38.415
on online services would of course require steps for users,

5637
05:19:38.875 --> 05:19:40.175
uh, to prove their age.

5638
05:19:40.315 --> 05:19:44.215
And the collection and use of personal information, uh, does

5639
05:19:44.215 --> 05:19:46.855
of course raise significant privacy issues.

5640
05:19:47.635 --> 05:19:50.735
Uh, as you've heard, age assurance is not just one thing

5641
05:19:51.155 --> 05:19:52.415
or indeed one technology,

5642
05:19:52.475 --> 05:19:54.375
but can be approached in different ways

5643
05:19:54.405 --> 05:19:55.935
that involve different uses

5644
05:19:56.435 --> 05:19:58.175
and types of personal information.

5645
05:19:58.705 --> 05:20:00.615
There is of course, age verification,

5646
05:20:00.625 --> 05:20:04.055
which relies on information from a trusted document, uh,

5647
05:20:04.125 --> 05:20:05.255
like a passport.

5648
05:20:06.065 --> 05:20:09.175
While modern digital ID systems aim to minimize

5649
05:20:09.175 --> 05:20:11.335
what is shared, it's critical to work through, uh,

5650
05:20:11.335 --> 05:20:13.415
the privacy and security issues.

5651
05:20:13.555 --> 05:20:16.535
And I'm very happy to talk about, uh, age verification.

5652
05:20:16.725 --> 05:20:21.095
Further. Age estimation relies on technologies

5653
05:20:21.095 --> 05:20:22.175
that estimate age.

5654
05:20:22.195 --> 05:20:24.895
And while that can be convenient for people, uh, well

5655
05:20:24.965 --> 05:20:28.045
outside the age restriction age, people like myself, uh,

5656
05:20:28.045 --> 05:20:29.605
the error rates for teenagers

5657
05:20:29.625 --> 05:20:32.365
and people who look different from those in the training

5658
05:20:32.395 --> 05:20:33.405
data can be high.

5659
05:20:33.465 --> 05:20:36.805
And that does create a risk of unfairness and exclusion.

5660
05:20:37.265 --> 05:20:39.565
And of course, the third category, age inference

5661
05:20:40.345 --> 05:20:43.205
relies on mining data about people, uh,

5662
05:20:43.315 --> 05:20:46.085
like their browsing patterns to try and infer their age.

5663
05:20:46.585 --> 05:20:49.485
Uh, we believe this approach could encourage further data

5664
05:20:49.485 --> 05:20:53.365
mining and profiling, which is of course, itself, uh, bad

5665
05:20:53.385 --> 05:20:54.525
for privacy, uh,

5666
05:20:54.585 --> 05:20:57.165
and indeed creates the risk of further data breaches

5667
05:20:58.075 --> 05:21:00.965
Overall, my view is that those privacy issues need to be,

5668
05:21:01.025 --> 05:21:04.845
uh, fully understood and worked through in a transparent

5669
05:21:05.065 --> 05:21:08.885
and consultative way before any such proposal is advanced.

5670
05:21:08.885 --> 05:21:11.085
Further, uh, all New Zealanders

5671
05:21:11.085 --> 05:21:12.965
and particularly young New Zealanders deserve

5672
05:21:12.965 --> 05:21:16.005
to fully understand, uh, the detailed policy case

5673
05:21:16.005 --> 05:21:19.605
before being asked to prove their age online.

5674
05:21:21.405 --> 05:21:23.405
I don't want to stray too far from, uh,

5675
05:21:23.545 --> 05:21:25.765
my regulatory swim lane, uh,

5676
05:21:25.765 --> 05:21:27.965
but for reasons that are pretty obvious, regulation

5677
05:21:27.965 --> 05:21:31.765
of the content of the online world is of course a hot topic.

5678
05:21:32.585 --> 05:21:34.925
Uh, and I acknowledge its Mental Health Awareness Week.

5679
05:21:34.985 --> 05:21:36.045
As I comment on this.

5680
05:21:36.205 --> 05:21:40.325
I presume, for example, uh, that no one wants social media

5681
05:21:40.425 --> 05:21:44.685
to become a place, uh, dominated by violence, uh, by hate,

5682
05:21:45.105 --> 05:21:46.205
uh, by despair.

5683
05:21:46.905 --> 05:21:50.965
Uh, but we cannot rely on hoping that that won't happen.

5684
05:21:51.195 --> 05:21:54.125
Hope is simply not a viable option.

5685
05:21:55.195 --> 05:21:58.645
Responsible self-policing in a manner consisted

5686
05:21:58.645 --> 05:22:02.285
with accepted norms, combined with smart regulation

5687
05:22:02.905 --> 05:22:04.485
is a more viable option.

5688
05:22:05.335 --> 05:22:07.365
Young people need to be protected online,

5689
05:22:07.465 --> 05:22:09.005
and regulation, along

5690
05:22:09.005 --> 05:22:11.485
with education plays a very important role

5691
05:22:11.545 --> 05:22:12.685
in keeping them safe.

5692
05:22:13.555 --> 05:22:16.845
However, regulation needs to be appropriately targeted,

5693
05:22:17.515 --> 05:22:20.525
effective, and indeed proportionate in relation

5694
05:22:20.525 --> 05:22:22.805
to the harms it seeks to address.

5695
05:22:24.155 --> 05:22:25.815
For example, I have, uh,

5696
05:22:25.815 --> 05:22:28.975
consistently argued since I became a privacy commissioner,

5697
05:22:28.975 --> 05:22:31.655
that our privacy regulatory framework should be modernized

5698
05:22:31.955 --> 05:22:35.335
to include the right to be forgotten, establishing a right,

5699
05:22:35.715 --> 05:22:38.335
uh, for people to have their information deleted, uh,

5700
05:22:38.335 --> 05:22:40.935
for example, to allow people a real choice to opt out

5701
05:22:40.935 --> 05:22:43.135
of marketing and data mining.

5702
05:22:44.475 --> 05:22:45.575
In conclusion, Mr. Chair,

5703
05:22:45.575 --> 05:22:47.495
New Zealand is a small open country

5704
05:22:47.675 --> 05:22:50.455
and open market, uh, with limited hard power.

5705
05:22:50.955 --> 05:22:52.895
We cannot necessarily lead,

5706
05:22:52.955 --> 05:22:56.535
but we have the luxury of seeing how policy approaches,

5707
05:22:56.535 --> 05:23:00.695
particularly around age assurance, play out overseas.

5708
05:23:00.835 --> 05:23:04.015
And indeed, it seems every week brings another piece

5709
05:23:04.075 --> 05:23:05.295
of policy research

5710
05:23:05.715 --> 05:23:08.495
or official government, uh, guidance in this area.

5711
05:23:09.315 --> 05:23:10.775
We can wait and see

5712
05:23:10.845 --> 05:23:14.535
what works overseas while doing our own thinking about

5713
05:23:14.565 --> 05:23:15.695
what institutions

5714
05:23:15.835 --> 05:23:19.695
and rules make particular sense in our context.

5715
05:23:19.905 --> 05:23:21.415
Thank you, Mr. Chair. Thank

5716
05:23:21.415 --> 05:23:22.535
You, Vanessa Wiener.

5717
05:23:22.835 --> 05:23:24.365
Uh, thank you very much for that.

5718
05:23:24.425 --> 05:23:26.445
Um, it's useful to hear your perspective.

5719
05:23:26.945 --> 05:23:30.365
Um, so we've heard from some age assurance providers

5720
05:23:30.385 --> 05:23:33.725
who have a third party, um, way of, uh,

5721
05:23:34.435 --> 05:23:36.605
providing verif, uh, you know, that to say

5722
05:23:36.605 --> 05:23:41.365
that this person is above this certain age that, um, is,

5723
05:23:41.825 --> 05:23:45.925
um, consented to be able to be used, doesn't,

5724
05:23:45.945 --> 05:23:48.285
it provides a token to the other side

5725
05:23:48.345 --> 05:23:52.285
so they don't have the data stored at a, at another place,

5726
05:23:52.505 --> 05:23:53.845
um, like the social media,

5727
05:23:54.345 --> 05:23:57.245
and it's also double-blinded, so they don't get, uh, any,

5728
05:23:57.505 --> 05:24:01.045
um, insight into what it is that the person who's asked

5729
05:24:01.045 --> 05:24:03.965
for the verification, um, is actually accessing.

5730
05:24:04.735 --> 05:24:06.685
Would that meet the requirements of, um,

5731
05:24:06.945 --> 05:24:08.485
the privacy settings in New Zealand?

5732
05:24:09.065 --> 05:24:10.525
Uh, so I, I, I,

5733
05:24:10.605 --> 05:24:11.845
I think what we're seeing here through you, Mr.

5734
05:24:11.855 --> 05:24:15.645
Chair, is, um, a bit of a discussion around if you're going

5735
05:24:15.645 --> 05:24:17.765
to go down the age assurance path, how

5736
05:24:18.305 --> 05:24:19.325
and what might happen.

5737
05:24:19.505 --> 05:24:22.325
And without going down the technology rabbit hole, uh,

5738
05:24:22.595 --> 05:24:25.285
what we need to think about a few steps

5739
05:24:25.285 --> 05:24:28.725
beyond these proposals is what will the response be?

5740
05:24:29.185 --> 05:24:30.885
Uh, there are obviously, and,

5741
05:24:30.905 --> 05:24:32.125
and young people, uh,

5742
05:24:32.145 --> 05:24:33.605
are particularly technologically clever.

5743
05:24:33.895 --> 05:24:37.925
There are approaches to try and get around age verification.

5744
05:24:38.145 --> 05:24:40.205
So, uh, what we are proposing is

5745
05:24:40.205 --> 05:24:42.325
that further work be done around those options.

5746
05:24:42.625 --> 05:24:45.605
Uh, some of them are better options than others, uh, to see

5747
05:24:45.665 --> 05:24:47.485
how strong, uh, they would be.

5748
05:24:48.065 --> 05:24:49.405
Uh, for example, in New Zealand,

5749
05:24:49.465 --> 05:24:52.085
we have our Digital Identity Services trust framework.

5750
05:24:52.085 --> 05:24:55.725
Mm-hmm. Um, there are, as you've just talked about, um,

5751
05:24:55.725 --> 05:24:58.445
options around what, what are known as zero knowledge proof,

5752
05:24:58.445 --> 05:25:00.885
where you don't actually have to provide any

5753
05:25:00.885 --> 05:25:03.565
of your personal information to the social media company.

5754
05:25:04.065 --> 05:25:06.645
Uh, you can just prove that you meet the requirements

5755
05:25:06.785 --> 05:25:08.725
of access without, for example,

5756
05:25:08.725 --> 05:25:10.045
providing your date of birth.

5757
05:25:10.425 --> 05:25:12.885
Uh, those options I think were worth considering.

5758
05:25:13.385 --> 05:25:14.885
Uh, but what I think we need

5759
05:25:14.885 --> 05:25:19.125
to see now is a further analysis of the results

5760
05:25:19.125 --> 05:25:20.325
of the studies that have been done.

5761
05:25:20.745 --> 05:25:22.965
Uh, for example, my colleague in Canada,

5762
05:25:23.145 --> 05:25:25.925
the privacy commissioner in Canada, has just, uh,

5763
05:25:25.955 --> 05:25:29.085
conducted a study into age assurance mechanisms.

5764
05:25:29.475 --> 05:25:32.845
It's those sorts of studies that I think, um, uh, officials

5765
05:25:33.065 --> 05:25:35.485
and others need to now analyze to see

5766
05:25:35.545 --> 05:25:38.205
how strong the protections are, uh, in there

5767
05:25:38.205 --> 05:25:41.765
because, uh, once in this world, you give up, uh, parts

5768
05:25:41.765 --> 05:25:43.325
of your privacy is there forever.

5769
05:25:43.945 --> 05:25:47.125
And the more and more, uh, that privacy has given up

5770
05:25:47.305 --> 05:25:48.485
to deliver on age assurance,

5771
05:25:48.665 --> 05:25:51.165
and let's face, it's not just young people, it's everybody

5772
05:25:51.385 --> 05:25:52.445
who has to prove their age,

5773
05:25:52.535 --> 05:25:53.725
which you would've heard many times.

5774
05:25:54.265 --> 05:25:57.125
Uh, you have created a honey pot of information

5775
05:25:57.225 --> 05:25:59.805
for very sophisticated cybercriminal criminals as well.

5776
05:26:02.005 --> 05:26:03.845
Yeah. Thank you. Um, so my question,

5777
05:26:03.845 --> 05:26:06.205
because, uh, you mentioned that you will be willing

5778
05:26:06.205 --> 05:26:08.925
to talk more about age verification, so maybe some of

5779
05:26:08.925 --> 05:26:10.005
that you've already covered,

5780
05:26:10.065 --> 05:26:13.325
but still I'll ask this question about the Australian age

5781
05:26:13.325 --> 05:26:15.045
assurance, uh, technology trial.

5782
05:26:15.585 --> 05:26:17.685
Um, obviously when we are looking at somebody

5783
05:26:17.685 --> 05:26:19.125
who is five versus 50 years,

5784
05:26:19.275 --> 05:26:20.685
it's easy to reject the difference.

5785
05:26:20.685 --> 05:26:24.765
Mm-hmm. The problem is we, it's for example, 15 versus 16

5786
05:26:24.765 --> 05:26:26.005
or 16 versus 17.

5787
05:26:26.005 --> 05:26:27.925
Right. And that's where the focus needs to be

5788
05:26:27.925 --> 05:26:29.285
for us when we are looking at it.

5789
05:26:29.585 --> 05:26:32.085
So very keen to explore your views

5790
05:26:32.085 --> 05:26:33.525
and insight, uh, about that,

5791
05:26:33.525 --> 05:26:35.245
because that means those people are required

5792
05:26:35.245 --> 05:26:37.965
to provide secondary level of information

5793
05:26:38.465 --> 05:26:39.885
to prove their age.

5794
05:26:40.405 --> 05:26:42.445
Hmm. And, and that is why, uh,

5795
05:26:42.585 --> 05:26:44.965
if I think about those three examples through Mr.

5796
05:26:44.965 --> 05:26:48.365
Chair that I talked about, uh, age verification,

5797
05:26:48.425 --> 05:26:51.965
age estimation, and aid in age inference, I think, uh,

5798
05:26:52.145 --> 05:26:53.845
age verification that's done in a way

5799
05:26:53.845 --> 05:26:55.205
that results in the least amount

5800
05:26:55.205 --> 05:26:56.725
